    "display_name": "Gesture Recognition",
    "description": "Classification of hand gestures such as thumbs up, thumbs down, pointing and waving using the MLC.\n\nThis example will allow you to classify hand gestures as they are performed, which range from thumbs up, thumbs down, pointing, or waving. The MLC smart sensor performs the classification in real time so that you do not need to wait for firmware-based gesture analysis. If you need to provide some data of your own or adjust the position of the sensors on the wrist, you can always clone the project into your workspace to retrain it yourself.\nTo use this example effectively, as in the case of Human Activity Recognition, the board should be placed on the outside of the wrist and remain strongly secured to it. Make sure it's orientated so that the USB port is facing upward toward the shoulder so that the LEDs and logos are visible and facing outward.",
